    {
      "id": "legend-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 25,
      "y": 577,
      "width": 1145,
      "height": 191,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#334155",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 826,
      "version": 3,
      "versionNonce": 543304000,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1749000000056,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "CHARGE (fixed order — idempotency stored LAST):  1 IdempotencyStore.TryGet (hit → return cached, no 2nd charge)  →  2 CardVault.IsValid  →  3 FraudScorer.Score (Block ≥80 → stop, never call bank)\n  →  4 CardNetworkGateway.Authorize (slow 1–3s; decline → Failed)  →  5 PaymentStore.Save(Authorized, v1)  →  6 LedgerService.Record [DEBIT customer / CREDIT suspense]  →  7 IdempotencyStore.Store LAST  →  8 WebhookService.Enqueue\n   WHY LAST: a crash before step 7 leaves NO key → retry safely redoes the whole charge (never \"already done\" for a charge that never finished)\n\nCAPTURE:  guard Status=Authorized  →  Gateway.Capture  →  read expectedVersion, set Captured/v2, PaymentStore.Update WHERE version=expected (CAS — loser gets CONCURRENT_UPDATE, retries)  →  ledger: DEBIT suspense / CREDIT merchant net + CREDIT platform fee\nSETTLE:   guard Status=Captured  →  v3  →  ledger: DEBIT merchant / CREDIT bank:settlement (the reconciliation anchor)\nREFUND:   guard refundCents ≤ RemainingRefundable (Captured−Refunded)  →  Gateway.Refund  →  PartiallyRefunded until cumulative = captured  →  ledger: 4 entries (return money + reverse fee)\n\nWEBHOOK:  persist PENDING before any HTTP → POST + HMAC-SHA256 → fail? backoff 10s→1m→5m→30m→2h→12h→24h (7 tries) then FAILED.  at-least-once; merchant dedupes on EventId.\nRECONCILE (nightly, out-of-band): match ledger bank:settlement credits vs bank EOD report by ref_id=payment_id → IN_LEDGER_ONLY (timing) · IN_BANK_ONLY (investigate) · MISMATCH (fee/FX).  IsBalanced() = Σ DEBIT == Σ CREDIT.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "legend",
      "originalText": "CHARGE (fixed order — idempotency stored LAST):  1 IdempotencyStore.TryGet (hit → return cached, no 2nd charge)  →  2 CardVault.IsValid  →  3 FraudScorer.Score (Block ≥80 → stop, never call bank)\n  →  4 CardNetworkGateway.Authorize (slow 1–3s; decline → Failed)  →  5 PaymentStore.Save(Authorized, v1)  →  6 LedgerService.Record [DEBIT customer / CREDIT suspense]  →  7 IdempotencyStore.Store LAST  →  8 WebhookService.Enqueue\n   WHY LAST: a crash before step 7 leaves NO key → retry safely redoes the whole charge (never \"already done\" for a charge that never finished)\n\nCAPTURE:  guard Status=Authorized  →  Gateway.Capture  →  read expectedVersion, set Captured/v2, PaymentStore.Update WHERE version=expected (CAS — loser gets CONCURRENT_UPDATE, retries)  →  ledger: DEBIT suspense / CREDIT merchant net + CREDIT platform fee\nSETTLE:   guard Status=Captured  →  v3  →  ledger: DEBIT merchant / CREDIT bank:settlement (the reconciliation anchor)\nREFUND:   guard refundCents ≤ RemainingRefundable (Captured−Refunded)  →  Gateway.Refund  →  PartiallyRefunded until cumulative = captured  →  ledger: 4 entries (return money + reverse fee)\n\nWEBHOOK:  persist PENDING before any HTTP → POST + HMAC-SHA256 → fail? backoff 10s→1m→5m→30m→2h→12h→24h (7 tries) then FAILED.  at-least-once; merchant dedupes on EventId.\nRECONCILE (nightly, out-of-band): match ledger bank:settlement credits vs bank EOD report by ref_id=payment_id → IN_LEDGER_ONLY (timing) · IN_BANK_ONLY (investigate) · MISMATCH (fee/FX).  IsBalanced() = Σ DEBIT == Σ CREDIT.",
      "lineHeight": 1.4,
      "index": "bI",
      "frameId": null,
      "autoResize": true
    }
